Hong Kong Appoints High Court Judges
HONG KONG , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The Hong Kong Judiciary announced Friday the new appointments of High Court Judges .
Judge Michael John Hartmann and Azizul Rahman Suffiad were appointed Judges of the Court of First Instance of the High Court .
Louis Tong Po-sun was appointed Chief Magistrate .
All appointments will come into effect on March 2 , 1998 .
The Chief Justice of the Court of Final Appeal Justice Andrew Li said Friday : " The appointees are all outstanding judges and judicial officers who bring a wealth of experience to the Judiciary . "
He said : " These appointments provide a substantial boost to the Judiciary in continuing to uphold the rule of law and to ensure the fair and efficient administration of justice . "
